deck: Writer, and the inspiration for Carl Kolchak
description:
John Keel, born Alva John Kiehle but known mainly as John A. Keel (March 25, 1930 – July 3, 2009) was an American writers and journalist who along with working as the science editor for Funk & Wagnalls encyclopedia, also wrote for television scripting for Get Smart, Man from U.N.C.L.E., Time Tunnel, and numerous game shows, and in the 60s became one of the most prominent investigators of Fortean phenomena devising the concept of Ultraterrestrials and writing such books as Strange Creatures from Time & Space and the Mothman Prophecies.


Like many freelance writers of the time he worked extensively in the comic book industry, manly for St. John and Ziff-Davis in the 50s, however as was common at the time no bylines or credit was given so the exact number of his contributions is impossible to say. In the 60s, during the Batman TV craze he also contributed a paperback original done like a comic book titled The Fickle Finger of Fate featuring a parody superhero called Satyr-Man.


Also of note, the creator of Carl Kolchak the Night Stalker based the character in part on John Keel.
name: John A. Keel

Valerio went to a comic book convention in Europe where he was recruited by C.B. Cebulski.

He loves Spider-Man and would love to draw him.

His art process starts with doodles on the script, then he sends his outlines to the writers for feedback.

The actual drawings are all done digitally.

He attended NYCC 2014 and was on Marvel's live broadcast of the event.
